abstract: Most voters taking part in New Hampshire's Democratic primary on Tuesday expressed deep dissatisfaction with President Donald Trump and said they would vote for the party's nominee  "regardless of who it is," according to an Edison Research exit poll.
snippet: Most voters taking part in New Hampshire's Democratic primary on Tuesday expressed deep dissatisfaction with President Donald Trump and said they would vote for the party's nominee  "regardless of who it is," according to an Edison Research exit p...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Most voters taking part in New Hampshire's Democratic primary on Tuesday expressed deep dissatisfaction with President Donald Trump and said they would vote for the party's nominee "regardless of who it is," according to an Edison Research exit poll.
headline_main: Angry With Trump, Most New Hampshire Democratic Primary Voters Will Back Party's Nominee 'Regardless': Edison Research
headline_print_headline: Angry With Trump, Most New Hampshire Democratic Primary Voters Will Back Party's Nominee 'Regardless': Edison Research

abstract: Democrats vying for the right to challenge U.S. President Donald Trump turned their focus on Wednesday to Nevada and South Carolina after Bernie Sanders solidified his front-runner status by narrowly beating Pete Buttigieg in New Hampshire.
snippet: Democrats vying for the right to challenge U.S. President Donald Trump turned their focus on Wednesday to Nevada and South Carolina after Bernie Sanders solidified his front-runner status by narrowly beating Pete Buttigieg in New Hampshire.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Democrats vying for the right to challenge U.S. President Donald Trump turned their focus on Wednesday to Nevada and South Carolina after Bernie Sanders solidified his front-runner status by narrowly beating Pete Buttigieg in New Hampshire.
headline_main: Democrats Turn Focus to Nevada and South Carolina After Sanders' Narrow Win in New Hampshire
headline_print_headline: Democrats Turn Focus to Nevada and South Carolina After Sanders' Narrow Win in New Hampshire

abstract: “This victory here is the beginning of the end for Donald Trump,” Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont told supporters celebrating in New Hampshire.

abstract: Venezuelan opposition leader Juan Guaidó is gearing up for the next stage of his campaign to oust President Nicolás Maduro following his return home from a tour abroad that included a meeting with his most important foreign ally — U.S. President Donald Trump.

lead_paragraph: CARACAS, Venezuela — Venezuelan opposition leader Juan Guaidó is gearing up for the next stage of his campaign to oust President Nicolás Maduro following his return home from a tour abroad that included a meeting with his most important foreign ally — U.S. President Donald Trump.
